  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "It leverages GRU [6] to capture the sequential information from users' interacted item logs.",
    "Specifically, it takes a user interaction sequence S = [𝑣 1, 𝑣 2,..., 𝑣 𝑡] as input, and then, converts them into a sequence of vectors [v 1, v 2,..., v 𝑡] using an item embedding table V. After that, a stack of GRU networks is applied in the embedding sequence and calculates a sequence of latent vectors [h 1, h 2,..., h 𝑡].",
    "Based on the latest latent vector h 𝑡, a feed-forward neural network is used to predict the user's preference scores at step 𝑡 + 1.r *,𝑡 +1 = 𝐹 𝐹 𝑁 (h 𝑡)(2)SASRec.",
    "It uses self-attention to capture the relationships between items in a user's interaction sequence.",
    "This design allows the model to focus on the most relevant previous interactions when making predictions, irrespective of their distance in the sequence."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "It leverages GRU [6] to capture the sequential information from users' interacted item logs."
  ]
